# {{.Name}}

A web application built with [Catuaba](https://github.com/dayvsonlima/catuaba) — a Rails-like framework for Go.

## Getting Started

```bash
# Install dependencies
go mod tidy

# Start the development server (with hot reload)
catuaba server
# or
make run
```

The server starts at `http://localhost:8080`.

## Available Commands

```bash
make run        # Start development server with hot reload
make build      # Build for production
make test       # Run tests
```

## Generating Code

```bash
# Generate a full CRUD scaffold
catuaba g scaffold Post title:string body:string

# Generate a model
catuaba g model User name:string email:string

# Generate a controller
catuaba g controller Auth login logout

# Generate a middleware
catuaba g middleware RateLimit

# Generate a service
catuaba g service Mailer

# Generate a database seed
catuaba g seed Users

# Generate a migration
catuaba g migration add_index_to_users
```

## Project Structure

```
{{.Name}}/
├── app/
│   ├── controllers/    # HTTP handlers (generated by scaffold/controller)
│   ├── models/         # GORM models (generated by model/scaffold)
│   └── services/       # Business logic (generated by service)
├── config/
│   ├── config.go       # Environment configuration
│   └── routes.go       # Route definitions
├── database/
│   ├── connection.go   # Database connection + SQL migration runner
│   ├── migrations/     # SQL migration files
│   └── seeds/          # Database seeds
├── middleware/          # HTTP middleware
├── .env                # Environment variables (do not commit)
├── .env.example        # Environment template
├── application.go      # Application entrypoint
├── Dockerfile          # Production Docker image
├── docker-compose.yml  # Development services
└── Makefile            # Build and dev commands
```
